Sentencas: The intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) whose operating temperature ranges from 873 K to 1073 K have attracted a lot of attention in recent years because of their decreased cost, improved efficiency, and increased turn on/off switch speed.
Titulo: Construction of Heterointerfaces with Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Kinetics for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Nevertheless, the reduced performance of the cathode when operating at the intermediate temperature range becomes a challenge, due to the reduced catalytic activity for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) on traditional cathode materials.
Titulo: Construction of Heterointerfaces with Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Kinetics for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Ideal cathodes are required to present efficient charge and oxygen transfer processes.
Titulo: Construction of Heterointerfaces with Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Kinetics for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Herein, by constructing heterointerfaces, we designed a novel composite cathode material PrSrFe0.5Co0.5O4-Pr0.4Sr0.6Fe0.5Co0.5O3 (PSFC214-113).
Titulo: Construction of Heterointerfaces with Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Kinetics for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: According to the X-ray diffraction patterns and high-resolution transmission electron microscopy, the PSFC214-113 composite material has been synthesized successfully.
Titulo: Construction of Heterointerfaces with Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Kinetics for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: As a SOFC cathode, PSFC214-113 maintains a high electronic conductivity and excellent chemical compatibility.
Titulo: Construction of Heterointerfaces with Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Kinetics for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Compared to single-phase materials, PSFC214-113 showed significantly lower electrochemical impedance spectroscopy values and the peak power density of cell reached a power density of 0.73 W cm(-2).
Titulo: Construction of Heterointerfaces with Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Kinetics for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The presence of heterointerfaces promoted electronic and oxygen migration which, in turn, enhanced the oxygen reduction kinetics and provided superior electrochemical performance to the material.
Titulo: Construction of Heterointerfaces with Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Kinetics for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Our results reveal that the construction of heterointerfaces is an effective strategy to enhance the oxygen reduction kinetics for the high-activity cathode.
Titulo: Construction of Heterointerfaces with Enhanced Oxygen Reduction Kinetics for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
